{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/after-effects-of-a-study-break","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>I covered my plans around a study break in a <a href=\"https://ltbringer.github.io/blog/study-breaks\">previous post</a>, concluded on 1st Jan 2021.</p>\n<p>My experience was highly positive, a quick set of points on: :</p>\n<h2 id=\"things-that-worked\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#things-that-worked\" aria-label=\"things that worked permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Things that worked</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Spending time on machine learning theory is a good investment; having a preference for directly usable knowledge initially made me shy away from research-papers and books. I found topics of relevance which otherwise, would only be addressed via intuition.</li>\n<li>I have a list of topics that are of interest and relevance. Usually, I would pick a dense topic that takes time to comprehend but the lack of relevance makes it very hard to follow regularly.</li>\n<li>Near the final few days, I was able to study for 2 hours. My concentration levels are embarrassing but being able to sit and study made me feel I am not a lost cause.</li>\n<li>Not to flex, but I managed to understand Bayes theorem and can derive it. The assumptions are not understood well but its a long way from mugging up the formula.</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"things-that-didnt\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#things-that-didnt\" aria-label=\"things that didnt permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Things that didn't</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>I focused on ML, I had prgoramming and ml checkpoints planned. Didn't work out.</li>\n<li>Need to study atleast 2-3 hours everyday to improve comprehension. I found it very difficult to keep myself from wandering off due to fatigue or excitement.</li>\n<li>Couldn't stick to a self-made syllabus. There were days where I couldn't keep myself away from work commitments. Add this to a squirrel's attention-span, and you get nothing covered in 24h.</li>\n<li>Due to inefficient use of time, I had to forego something even within ML. Luckily, I picked coverage over depth. It matched my attention span and also helped me understand if I should pick and rank these topics for a deeper dive.</li>\n<li>There were topics that I covered and tried to understand but even after spending hours I couldn't get a grip on the underlying concepts. No notes were written for these topics.</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"units-skimmed\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#units-skimmed\" aria-label=\"units skimmed permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Units skimmed</h2>\n<p>I covered <a href=\"https://www.amazon.in/Pattern-Recognition-Learning-Information-Statistics/dp/0387310738\">Pattern Recognition and Machine Learning</a> only during this break. The units, page numbers etc are in-sync with the above resource.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Ch1: Introduction</p>\n<ul>\n<li>1.5: Decision Theory</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Ch 4: Linear models for Classification</li>\n<li>Ch 5: Neural Networks</li>\n<li>\n<p>Ch 12: Continuous Latent Variables</p>\n<ul>\n<li>12.1: Principal component analysis</li>\n<li>12.2: Probabilistic PCA</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Ch 13: Sequential Data</p>\n<ul>\n<li>13.1: Markov Models</li>\n<li>13.2: Hidden Markov Models</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"a-page-from-the-notebook\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#a-page-from-the-notebook\" aria-label=\"a page from the notebook permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>A page from the notebook</h2>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 690px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/blog/static/3c3e665f400cf3f5584485defe840431/c06f5/linear_models_for_clf_1.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gats